The paper deals with the spectral properties of graphs with a core-periphery structure, which is a common feature of many complex systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as social and information networks (cs.SI), graph theory (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistical learning (cs.ST). The paper also mentions the context of graph partitioning and community detection, which could indicate a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) or data mining (cs.DM). Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI and cs.SD, followed by cs.DM, cs.NI, and cs.LG.
